Edits applied to [content/papers/macroscopic.prediction.md](/home/dave/Projects/jaynes-archive/content/papers/macroscopic.prediction.md).

Concise summary of what changed:
- Fixed markdown structure/readability by adding blank-line paragraph boundaries where paragraphs were visually merged.
- Normalized display math layout for Hugo+KaTeX by separating inline-adjacent `$$...$$` blocks onto standalone lines with surrounding blank lines.
- Fixed unresolved equation reference mapping by splitting the former combined two-line equation into:
  - `\tag{36}` for `\dot{q} = ...`
  - `\tag{37}` for `\dot{R} = ...`
  so in-text references to (37) now resolve correctly.
- Normalized citations to markdown footnote format:
  - In-text `[n]`/`[1,2]` -> `[^n]`/`[^1][^2]`
  - Reference entries converted to `[^n]: ...`
- Removed the extraneous orphan footnote line at the end (`[^1]: In *Complex Systems...*`) that was not part of the paper body flow.

Self-check completed:
- Intended paragraph breaks are blank-line separated.
- No unresolved in-text equation reference to missing display-equation numbers remains (notably Eq. 37 is now present).
